{"ts": "2026-06-11T09:45:01.090907+07:00", "tool": "codex", "event": "UserPromptSubmit", "session_id": "019eb1ff-2cb4-7491-a93c-eb42b94698c0", "model": "gpt-5.5", "repo": "C2-App-079", "branch": "feat/environment-dashboard", "commit": "4d5eebc", "student": "linhdo.tech@gmail.com", "prompt": "Cursor Logic Bug\nIn _decode_chat_cursor, the code checks decoded.chat_id <= 0. However, if the database uses a non-positive ID (though rare) or if the cursor was generated for an empty set, this might trigger a 400 error. More importantly, the _encode_chat_cursor is called using chats[-1]. If the result set is empty, this will raise an IndexError before the if has_more and chats check in list_chats.\n\nif decoded.version != 2 or decoded.chat_id <= 0 or not valid_search:", "turn_id": "019eb491-97e8-7dd1-86b8-5c7bd30641a7", "transcript_path": "/Users/linhdt/.codex/sessions/2026/06/10/rollout-2026-06-10T21-45-50-019eb1ff-2cb4-7491-a93c-eb42b94698c0.jsonl"}
